    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "D&C",
        "delineation": "Section",
        "number": 1,
        "summary": "1\u20137, The voice of warning is to all people; 8\u201316, Apostasy and wickedness precede the Second Coming; 17\u201323, Joseph Smith is called to restore to earth the Lord's truths and powers; 24\u201333, The Book of Mormon is brought forth and the true Church is established; 34\u201336, Peace will be taken from the earth; 37\u201339, Search these commandments.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Hearken, O ye people of my church, saith the voice of him who dwells on high, and whose eyes are upon all men; yea, verily I say: Hearken ye people from afar; and ye that are upon the islands of the sea, listen together.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 32:1; Isa. 1:2; 49:1.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 27:3 (1\u20138); D&C 20:1; 21:3. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Head of the Church.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 33:18; Amos 9:8; D&C 38:7 (7\u20138). TG\u00a0God, Omniscience of.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For verily the voice of the Lord is unto all men, and there is none to escape; and there is no eye that shall not see, neither ear that shall not hear, neither heart that shall not be penetrated.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 65:2; Micah 1:2; D&C 1:34 (34\u201335); 18:28 (26\u201328); 39:15; 42:58; 68:8; 138:30. TG\u00a0Israel, Mission of.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 34:22; 1\u00a0Thes. 5:3.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Conversion.",
                        "start": 127,
                        "end": 130
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Heart.",
                        "start": 160,
                        "end": 165
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the rebellious shall be pierced with much sorrow; for their iniquities shall be spoken upon the housetops, and their secret acts shall be revealed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rebellion.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Conscience.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 32:10. TG\u00a0Sorrow.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 28:13; Isa. 57:12 (11\u201312); Luke 8:17; 12:3; 2\u00a0Ne. 27:11; Morm. 5:8; D&C 88:108; 112:25 (25\u201326).",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the voice of warning shall be unto all people, by the mouths of my disciples, whom I have chosen in these last days.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 3:21 (17\u201321); D&C 63:37. TG\u00a0Israel, Mission of; Mission of Latter-day Saints; Warn.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Priesthood, Authority.",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 100
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Last Days.",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 119
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they shall go forth and none shall stay them, for I the Lord have commanded them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Missionary Work.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, this is mine authority, and the authority of my servants, and my preface unto the book of my commandments, which I have given them to publish unto you, O inhabitants of the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Authority of; Priesthood, Authority.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 33:14; 42:13; 51:4.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 113
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 13:49; D&C 72:21.",
                        "start": 142,
                        "end": 149
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Joel 1:2; Micah 1:2.",
                        "start": 162,
                        "end": 173
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 2
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, fear and tremble, O ye people, for what I the Lord have decreed in them shall be fulfilled.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 5:29; Eccl. 12:13.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezra 9:4.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 10:22 (21\u201334); Matt. 24:34.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 34:16 (16\u201317).",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 101
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And verily I say unto you, that they who go forth, bearing these tidings unto the inhabitants of the earth, to them is power given to seal both on earth and in heaven, the unbelieving and rebellious;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 68:12. TG\u00a0Priesthood, Keys of; Sealing.",
                        "start": 134,
                        "end": 138
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rebellion.",
                        "start": 188,
                        "end": 198
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, verily, to seal them up unto the day when the wrath of God shall be poured out upon the wicked without measure\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Cor. 1:14.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 11:4 (3\u20139); Eccl. 8:12 (11\u201312); Rev. 18:6 (6\u20138).",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Nahum 1:3; Mosiah 16:2; JS\u2014M 1:55 (31, 55).",
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 99
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Unto the day when the Lord shall come to recompense unto every man according to his work, and measure to every man according to the measure which he has measured to his fellow man.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Day of the Lord.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 11:31; Isa. 65:6 (6\u20137, 11); Ezek. 7:4; Mosiah 12:1; D&C 56:19. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Judge.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 34:11; Prov. 24:12; Isa. 59:18; Alma 9:28; 36:15; 41:3 (2\u20135); 42:27; D&C 6:33.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 88
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 7:2; Luke 6:38.",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 101
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore the voice of the Lord is unto the ends of the earth, that all that will hear may hear:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Prepare ye, prepare ye for that which is to come, for the Lord is nigh;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Millennium, Preparing a People for.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 2:1; 49:28; 58:65; 68:11; 68:35; 84:119. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Second Coming.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the anger of the Lord is kindled, and his sword is bathed in heaven, and it shall fall upon the inhabitants of the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 63:6. TG\u00a0Anger; God, Indignation of.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 21:3; D&C 35:14; 84:114; 85:3.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the arm of the Lord shall be revealed; and the day cometh that they who will not hear the voice of the Lord, neither the voice of his servants, neither give heed to the words of the prophets and apostles, shall be cut off from among the people;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 40:10 (5\u201310); D&C 45:47; 56:1.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zech. 14:1.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 33:31 (30\u201333); Matt. 11:15; Heb. 5:11 (11\u201314); 2\u00a0Ne. 9:31; Mosiah 26:28; Moses 6:27. TG\u00a0Hardheartedness; Haughtiness.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 89
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prophets, Rejection of.",
                        "start": 138,
                        "end": 146
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 11:2. TG\u00a0Disobedience.",
                        "start": 161,
                        "end": 165
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostles.",
                        "start": 199,
                        "end": 207
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 3:23 (22\u201323); Alma 50:20; D&C 5:5; 50:8; 56:3 (1, 3\u20134).",
                        "start": 218,
                        "end": 225
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For they have strayed from mine ordinances, and have broken mine everlasting covenant;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Josh. 23:16 (15\u201316); Isa. 24:5; D&C 3:6 (6\u20138); 104:52.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Ordinance.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of Individuals; Apostasy of Israel; Apostasy of the Early Christian Church.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 44:7. TG\u00a0New and Everlasting Covenant.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They seek not the Lord to establish his righteousness, but every man walketh in his own way, and after the image of his own god, whose image is in the likeness of the world, and whose substance is that of an idol, which waxeth old and shall perish in Babylon, even Babylon the great, which shall fall.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 6:33.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking in Darkness.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 76
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 53:6; Jer. 44:17.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 87
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 6:12; D&C 82:6; Moses 8:29.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 91
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 20:4; Isa. 41:29 (24, 29); 3\u00a0Ne. 21:17 (17\u201319). TG\u00a0Idolatry.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 112
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 50:9.",
                        "start": 227,
                        "end": 230
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 21:9; 48:14; D&C 64:24; 133:14. TG\u00a0Babylon; Worldliness.",
                        "start": 251,
                        "end": 258
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, I the Lord, knowing the calamity which should come upon the inhabitants of the earth, called upon my servant Joseph Smith, Jun., and spake unto him from heaven, and gave him commandments;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Foreknowledge of.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 24:6 (1\u20136).",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Called of God.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 108
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Servant.",
                        "start": 112,
                        "end": 119
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Revelation.",
                        "start": 144,
                        "end": 149
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 1:30 (23\u201328, 30).",
                        "start": 185,
                        "end": 197
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 3
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And also gave commandments to others, that they should proclaim these things unto the world; and all this that it might be fulfilled, which was written by the prophets\u2014",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The weak things of the world shall come forth and break down the mighty and strong ones, that man should not counsel his fellow man, neither trust in the arm of flesh\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Chr. 29:1; Acts 4:13; 1\u00a0Cor. 1:27; 1\u00a0Ne. 7:8 (8\u201318); D&C 35:13; 124:1. TG\u00a0Meek.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 8:10.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 108
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 44:6 (6\u20138); Jer. 9:4; 17:5; 2\u00a0Ne. 28:31 (30\u201331). TG\u00a0Trust Not in the Arm of Flesh.",
                        "start": 141,
                        "end": 146
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But that every man might speak in the name of God the Lord, even the Savior of the world;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Authority.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That faith also might increase in the earth;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That mine everlasting covenant might be established;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 39:11. TG\u00a0Covenants; New and Everlasting Covenant.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That the fulness of my gospel might be proclaimed by the weak and the simple unto the ends of the world, and before kings and rulers.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 15:29.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gospel.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Missionary Work.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 1:27 (26\u201329). TG\u00a0Strength.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Kings, Earthly.",
                        "start": 116,
                        "end": 121
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 119:46; Matt. 10:18; Acts 9:15; D&C 124:3 (3, 16, 107).",
                        "start": 126,
                        "end": 132
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, I am God and have spoken it; these commandments are of me, and were given unto my servants in their weakness, after the manner of their language, that they might come to understanding.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 51:16; 2\u00a0Ne. 33:10 (10\u201311); Moro. 10:27 (27\u201329).",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 31:3; Ether 12:39; D&C 67:5. TG\u00a0Language.",
                        "start": 144,
                        "end": 152
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 50:12. TG\u00a0Understanding.",
                        "start": 178,
                        "end": 191
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And inasmuch as they erred it might be made known;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 29:24.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And inasmuch as they sought wisdom they might be instructed;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 8:16 (16\u201317); D&C 42:68. TG\u00a0Wisdom.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Teachable.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And inasmuch as they sinned they might be chastened, that they might repent;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastening; Reproof.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Repent.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 75
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And inasmuch as they were humble they might be made strong, and blessed from on high, and receive knowledge from time to time.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Humility; Poor in Spirit.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Knowledge.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And after having received the record of the Nephites, yea, even my servant Joseph Smith, Jun., might have power to translate through the mercy of God, by the power of God, the Book of Mormon.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 3:12.",
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 124
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mercy.",
                        "start": 137,
                        "end": 142
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Book of Mormon.",
                        "start": 176,
                        "end": 190
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And also those to whom these commandments were given, might have power to lay the foundation of this church, and to bring it forth out of obscurity and out of darkness, the only true and living church upon the face of the whole earth, with which I, the Lord, am well pleased, speaking unto the church collectively and not individually\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 1:17 (4\u20135, 17\u201318).",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Restoration of the Gospel.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 107
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Darkness, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 159,
                        "end": 167
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 14:33; Eph. 4:5 (3\u201313). TG\u00a0Church.",
                        "start": 194,
                        "end": 200
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 38:10.",
                        "start": 267,
                        "end": 274
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 50:4.",
                        "start": 276,
                        "end": 284
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For I the Lord cannot look upon sin with the least degree of allowance;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lev. 5:17 (17\u201319); D&C 24:2. TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Nevertheless, he that repents and does the commandments of the Lord shall be forgiven;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Repent.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 19:16.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 65:3; D&C 58:42 (42\u201343). TG\u00a0Forgive.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he that repents not, from him shall be taken even the light which he has received; for my Spirit shall not always strive with man, saith the Lord of Hosts.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 3:11; 121:37 (34\u201337).",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 25:29 (29\u201330); D&C 60:3 (2\u20133).",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Spirit of; Holy Ghost, Loss of.",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 100
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 6:3; 1\u00a0Sam. 28:15; Isa. 57:16; Moro. 9:4.",
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 124
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And again, verily I say unto you, O inhabitants of the earth: I the Lord am willing to make these things known unto all flesh;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 45:19. TG\u00a0Testimony.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 110
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 1:2; 18:28 (26\u201328); 39:15; 42:58.",
                        "start": 116,
                        "end": 119
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
